article.description: Saint Joseph's comes back to beat Davidson 75-70
article.headline: Saint Joseph's comes back to beat Davidson 75-70
article.linkText: Saint Joseph's comes back to beat Davidson 75-70
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- DeAndre Bembry scored 21 points, Aaron Brown added a career-high 20 and Saint Joseph's held off Davidson in the final seconds to preserve a 75-70 comeback on Saturday. The Hawks trailed 41-28 at the break after shooting 11 of 32 in the first half. They scored 11 straight points to start the second, and Bembry's layup put St. Joseph's ahead with 12:59 to go. Davidson trailed 68-57 with 1:44 left to play, but an 8-0 run -- including six points from Peyton Aldridge -- had the Wildcats within three points. Later, Brian Sullivan hit a 3-pointer for a two-point game with 21 seconds left. St. Joseph's made 3 of 6 free throws in the final seconds and the Wildcats missed their final two shot attempts. Bembry finished with 17 rebounds, and Isaiah Miles added 13 points for the Hawks (9-11, 3-5 Atlantic-10). Aldridge led Davidson (14-5, 5-3) with 24 points.
